Sec. 251.001. POLICY. It is the policy of this state to
conserve, protect, and encourage the development and improvement of
its agricultural land for the production of food and other
agricultural products. It is the purpose of this chapter to reduce
the loss to the state of its agricultural resources by limiting the
circumstances under which agricultural operations may be regulated or
considered to be a nuisance.
Added by Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 2595, ch. 693, Sec. 21, eff. Aug.
31, 1981.

